<table align="center" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0" ><tr ><td valign="top" width="650" ><div class="mktEditable" id="left-column" ><p><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; color: #000000; font-size: 14px;">Dear Honeywell Repair and Overhaul Customer,</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; color: #000000; font-size: 14px;">Our records indicted that your company does not currently have a credit agreement with Honeywell. If this is incorrect, please disregard this message.</span></p>
<p><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;">Beginning February 1,&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 14px;">2014, customers without established credit terms will need to pay the full invoice amount before we can service their unit. Here&rsquo;s how the process will work:</span></span></p>
<ul>
<li><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 14px;"><span style="color: #000000;">Log onto your </span><a href="https://myaerospace.honeywell.com/wps/portal/">MyAerospace</a> <span style="color: #000000;">account </span></span></li>
<li><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; color: #000000; font-size: 14px;">Select repair</span></li>
<li><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; color: #000000; font-size: 14px;">Complete the <u>part number </u>field</span></li>
<li><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; color: #000000; font-size: 14px;">The flat rate and repair tiers for the part number will appear on the screen </span>
<ul>
<li><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; color: #000000; font-size: 14px;">If no figure is displayed, the part number is either under a contractual agreement or no flat rate has yet been established, in which case repairs will be charged based on time and materials</span></li>
<li><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; color: #000000; font-size: 14px;">Enter the price into your purchase order and send it with the part to be repaired to the Honeywell Repair &amp; Overhaul facility identified</span></li>
<li><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; color: #000000; font-size: 14px;">A Honeywell Customer Service Representative will then send you payment instructions </span>
<ul>
<li><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; color: #000000; font-size: 14px;">Repair of your unit will begin after monies are received. <strong>Your repair unit will be returned to you &lsquo;as is&rsquo; if payment is not received within 10 business days.</strong></span><strong>ï»¿</strong></li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<p><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 14px;"><span style="color: #000000;">Our goal is to provide you with the best possible Repair &amp; Overhaul services available and to make every interaction with Honeywell as easy for you as possible. Ease-of-use was our guiding principle in redesigning the </span><a href="https://myaerospace.honeywell.com/wps/portal/">MyAerospace</a> <span style="color: #000000;">portal and we welcome your feedback on how we can make it even more user-friendly.&nbsp;</span></span><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; color: #000000; font-size: 14px;">&nbsp;</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 14px;"><span style="color: #000000;">If you have questions about the new payment in advance for repairs or the flat rate program, please contact your Honeywell Customer Service Representative or send an email to </span><a href="mailto:debra.malicki@honeywell.com">debra.malicki@honeywell.com</a>.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 14px;">Best regards,<br /><br /></span><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 14px;">Honeywell Aftermarket Programs<br /></span><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 14px;">Honeywell Aerospace<span style="color: #1f497d;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p></div>
